column59: Our librarian provides formal instruction on library resources and good research practices. She knows YA literature, discusses books with our kids and makes recommendations based on their interests. Our librarian manages a lunchtime maker space and teaches in an after-school gifted and talented program. Our librarian is also our "in-house" technology resource - she comes to our classrooms to help solve computer problems, manages classroom technology used by students, and conveys all technology help requests to the IT department (we aren't allowed to send the requests ourselves). She opens her classroom space (the library) to a number of activities, participates in PLCs, and for me, is a good friend and listening ear.
